  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Enrolled Nurse",
  "description": "<p>Dover Park Hospice is on an inspiring journey of growth and transformation. As we adopt new systems, enhance our processes, and discover more effective ways of working together, we are committed to creating an even more compassionate and supportive space for our patients and their loved ones.</p><p>We are looking for a compassionate and dedicated team player who is passionate about providing quality patient care as an Enrolled Nurse.<br /></p><p>Job Responsibility:</p><ul><li><p>Provide comfort care to patients with terminally illness and end-stage organ failure under the supervision of Staff Nurse and Senior Enrolled Nurse.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Assist Staff Nurse in performing comprehensive palliative care assessment.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Provide guidance and supervision of new Nursing Aides.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Participate in quality improvement activities.</p></li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li><p>National Institute Technical Education (ITE): Certificate in Nursing Enrolled Nurse </p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Valid practicing license with Singapore Nursing Board.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Minimum 2 years in clinical experience and palliative care setting.</p></li></ul>",
